    "body": "### Problem\n\nMemory leak on SIGHUP with remote client attached.\n\nThe following change is need to find the actual position of the leak:\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/memory.c b/src/nvim/memory.c\nindex 0623834fe4..b025036145 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/memory.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/memory.c\n@@ -674,7 +674,7 @@ void *mergesort_list(void *head, MergeSortGetFunc get_next, MergeSortSetFunc set\n   return head;\n }\n \n-#define REUSE_MAX 4\n+#define REUSE_MAX 0\n \n static struct consumed_blk *arena_reuse_blk;\n static size_t arena_reuse_blk_count = 0;\n```\n\nASAN log after applying the change above:\n```\n\n=================================================================\n==2089849==ERROR: LeakSanitizer: detected memory leaks\n\nDirect leak of 4096 byte(s) in 1 object(s) allocated from:\n    #0 0x5567b58d2b05 in malloc (**/build/bin/nvim+0xd95b05) (BuildId: 81a1dbb637804ae755a5f6298ff4cf1ae5401cd5)\n    #1 0x5567b65418c4 in try_malloc **/src/nvim/memory.c:113:15\n    #2 0x5567b6541b24 in xmalloc **/src/nvim/memory.c:147:15\n    #3 0x5567b65445cd in alloc_block **/src/nvim/memory.c:717:12\n    #4 0x5567b5fcfbf3 in rstream_init **/src/nvim/event/rstream.c:37:20\n    #5 0x5567b5bc89c0 in channel_from_connection **/src/nvim/channel.c:508:3\n    #6 0x5567b6610590 in connection_cb **/src/nvim/msgpack_rpc/server.c:280:3\n    #7 0x5567b5fd88fb in connection_event **/src/nvim/event/socket.c:172:3\n    #8 0x5567b5fd6c4e in connection_cb **/src/nvim/event/socket.c:178:3\n    #9 0x5567b7137375 in uv__server_io **/.deps/build/src/libuv/src/unix/stream.c:528:3\n    #10 0x5567b7141cac in uv__io_poll **/.deps/build/src/libuv/src/unix/linux.c:1565:11\n    #11 0x5567b7125d07 in uv_run **/.deps/build/src/libuv/src/unix/core.c:460:5\n    #12 0x5567b5fbf0e7 in loop_uv_run **/src/nvim/event/loop.c:59:3\n    #13 0x5567b5fbed64 in loop_poll_events **/src/nvim/event/loop.c:80:26\n    #14 0x5567b678ff31 in inbuf_poll **/src/nvim/os/input.c:515:3\n    #15 0x5567b678f962 in input_get **/src/nvim/os/input.c:154:18\n    #16 0x5567b6b59b08 in state_enter **/src/nvim/state.c:79:7\n    #17 0x5567b66234f4 in normal_enter **/src/nvim/normal.c:523:3\n    #18 0x5567b63a3e50 in main **/src/nvim/main.c:656:3\n    #19 0x7f64cd227674 in __libc_start_call_main /usr/src/debug/glibc/glibc/csu/../sysdeps/nptl/libc_start_call_main.h:58:16\n    #20 0x7f64cd227728 in __libc_start_main /usr/src/debug/glibc/glibc/csu/../csu/libc-start.c:360:3\n    #21 0x5567b57cf004 in _start (**/build/bin/nvim+0xc92004) (BuildId: 81a1dbb637804ae755a5f6298ff4cf1ae5401cd5)\n\nSUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: 4096 byte(s) leaked in 1 allocation(s).\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Build Nvim with ASAN and run `nvim --clean`.\n2. Start a remote TUI (or GUI) client in another terminal and attach to the server.\n3. Close the terminal containing the server.\n4. Memory leak in the server.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo memory leak.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-1546+ge87f2d1cf9\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.43.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
